question: Which Indian missile has recently been successfully test fired from a mobile launcher at night?
explanation: India successfully testfired on November 20night its indigenously developed nuclear capable surface-to-surface Prithvi-2 missile as part of a user trial by the Army from a test range off Odisha coast, from the Interim Test Range (ITR) at Chandipur. The trial of the missile, which has a strike range of 350 km, was carried out from a mobile launcher from launch complex-3 of the ITR between 7 pm to 7.15 pm.
